author: National Geographic
description:
When Jaws was released in 1975, it changed both cinema and our relationship with sharks forever. Now, rediscover this iconic film with never-before-seen footage from Steven Spielberg’s archives, interviews with Hollywood’s top filmmakers, and insights from the original cast and crew.

Jaws @ 50: The Definitive Inside Story premieres Thursday, July 10 at 9/8c on National Geographic. Streaming next day on Disney+ and Hulu.
title: Discover the history of Jaws from the filmmakers it inspired

author: National Geographic
description:
Espresso art, grappa shots, and exclusive social clubs: Jo Franco is uncovering London’s hidden Little Italy in a wild scavenger hunt. From perfecting espresso making to crafting Michelin-star pasta, Jo digs into the city’s most authentic Italian spots that even the locals don’t know about.
